Sff„ thinking that morsus must have something to define it, reads morsus tamen ex contractione quadam animi relinquentur (quadam with some MS support); but Knh. points out that et often has an explanatory force. con- tractiuncula is only a depreciatory dimi- nutive of contractio, which occurs several times in the sing. in this sense, i 37, 90; iv 6, 143 31, 66, 67.
